theorem
Th5: (((((a <> ( 0 ) & b <> ( 0 )) & m <> ( 0 )) & a,m are_relative_prime ) & b,m are_relative_prime ) implies m,( ( a * b ) mod m ) are_relative_prime )
proof
assume that
A1: a <> ( 0 )
and
A2: b <> ( 0 )
and
A3: m <> ( 0 )
and
A4: (a,m are_relative_prime  & b,m are_relative_prime );
( a * b ),m are_relative_prime  by A1,A3,A4,EULER_1:14;
then A5: ( ( a * b ) gcd m ) = 1 by INT_2:def 3;
consider t being Nat such that A6: ( a * b ) = ( ( m * t ) + ( ( a * b ) mod m ) ) and ( ( a * b ) mod m ) < m by A3,NAT_D:def 2;
( a * b ) <> ( a * ( 0 ) ) by A1,A2,XCMPLX_1:5;
then ( ( ( a * b ) + ( ( - t ) * m ) ) gcd m ) = ( ( a * b ) gcd m ) by EULER_1:16;
hence thesis by A6,A5,INT_2:def 3;
end;
